President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for judicial positions in the United States. Robert J. Colville and Stephanie L. Haines have been nominated to serve as District Judges on the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Pennsylvania. Jason K. Pulliam has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Texas. Matthew H. Solomson and David A. Tapp have been nominated to serve as Judges on the U.S. Court of Federal Claims. Timothy J. Downing has been nominated to serve as the United States Attorney for the Western District of Oklahoma. Michael East has been nominated to serve as the United States Marshal for the Eastern District of North Carolina, and Brent R. Bunn has been nominated to serve as the United States Marshal for the District of Idaho.